  "rationale": "<p>Choice B is correct. It&rsquo;s given that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 3 x, equals x minus 6\"></span> for all values of <span class=\"italic\">x</span>. If <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 x equals 6\"></span>, then <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 3 x\"></span> will equal <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 6\"></span>. Dividing both sides of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"3 x equals 6 \"></span> by 3 gives <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 2\"></span>. Therefore, substituting 2 for <span class=\"italic\">x</span> in the given equation yields <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of, open parenthesis, 3 times 2, close parenthesis, equals 2 minus 6\"></span>, which can be rewritten as <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"f of 6, equals negative 4\"></span>.<p>Choice A is incorrect. This is the value of the constant in the given equation for <span class=\"italic\">f</span>. Choice C is incorrect and may result from substituting <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 6\"></span>, rather than <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"x equals 2\"></sp